textBody:
Kishka can be:

Food

* Kishka (food) or Kishke, various types of sausage or stuffed intestine with a filling made from a combination of meat and meal, often a grain

People

* Kyszka (family), a szlachta family in the Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth
* Jan Kiszka
* Janusz Kiszka

Other uses

* Intestine or gut, in East Slavic languages, also used in English-language Yiddishisms
* Kishka (prison cell), a type of cell in Soviet political prisons
